<H2> Bruno Ciciani's Biographical Sketch </H2>
<BR>
<UL> <LI> Bruno Ciciani is a full professor of Computer Engineering at the University of Rome "La Sapienza". His research intersests include concurrent computing, fault tolerance, computer architecture, manufacturing yield prediction, performance and dependability evaluation of distributed and parallel computing systems. In these fields he obtained results that have been published in qualified journals as: IEEE Trans. on Computers, IEEE Trans. on Reliability, IEEE Trans. on Computer Aided Design, IEEE Trans. on Software Engineering, IEEE Trans. on Knowledge and Data Engineering and IEEE Trans. on Communications. He has also written books, two of them have been published by Mc Graw Hills and IEEE Computer Society Press. 
	Ciciani received a MS degree in Electronic Engineering from the University of Rome "La Sapienza" in the 1980. He spent more than one year as visiting researcher at the IBM Thomas J. Watson Research Center (N.Y.). He is a member of the IEEE Computer Society.

</UL><P><P>


